Step 1: Find the current age of your sister. In this case, she is 6.

Step 2: Find the age at which your sister was half of your own age. In this case, she was half of 80, which is 40.

Step 3: Subtract the current age of your sister from the age at which she was half of your own age. In this case, the current age of her is 6, and the age at which she was half of your own age is 40. Therefore, she is 24.

Therefore, my sister is now 24 years old..
